<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4894330>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 10. Areca triginticollina. A. Apical portion of leaf. B. Middle and basal portion of leaf. C. Basal portion of leaf and leaf sheath showing absence of petiole. D. Prophyll with disintegrating fibrous mass. E. Inflorescence. F. Details of rachilla showing staminate and pistilate flowers in bud and their arrangements. G. Pistillate flowers at anthesis on rachillae. H, I. Staminate flower whole and in section. J. Pistillate flower in section. Scale bar: A–C = 6 cm; D, E = 3 cm; F = 1.5 cm; G = 2.5 cm; H–J = 4 mm. A–F, H–J from Witono et al. 150; G from Gundersen et al. 15. Drawn by Lucy T. Smith." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4894330/files/figure.png" .

